description: These American TV institutions, which mix humor and politics, have traditionally been critical of the president-elect.
title: US presidential election: Between cynicism and bitterness, late night shows take note of Trump's victory

description: The Caribbean nation has long struggled with political instability, poverty, natural disasters and gang violence. But conditions sharply worsened at the end of February when armed groups launched coordinated attacks in the capital Port-au-Prince, saying they wanted to overthrow then-prime minister Ariel Henry.
title: New Haiti PM sworn in, promises to 'restore security'

description: Flight 951 from Fort Lauderdale, Florida to Port-au-Prince was diverted and landed safely in neighboring Dominican Republic, Spirit said in a statement. The Haitian capital is largely controlled by powerful, well-armed gangs.
title: Spirit Airlines says flight to Haiti's capital hit by gunfire

description: Israeli Foreign Minister Gideon Saar said any agreement would have to include enforcement mechanisms to prevent Hezbollah from reconstituting its military infrastructure near the border.
title: Israeli minister reports some progress toward cease-fire but Hezbollah unaware

description: Nearly 200 nations agreed on a number of crucial ground rules for a credible, UN-backed international carbon market, enabling countries to trade high-quality carbon credits to help meet climate targets.
title: COP29: Nations approve new standards on carbon markets

description: 'In Sudan, a total war' (1/8). Since April 15, 2023, the conflict between General al-Burhan's forces and General Hemedti's militias may have claimed the lives of over 150,000 civilians. Le Monde reports from the army-controlled areas of Sudan in the first part of a series on a country where the hopes of the 2019 revolution have been shattered by war, now fueling the world's worst humanitarian crisis.
title: War in Sudan: Death strikes at every corner  in devastated Khartoum

description: The ruling challenges Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni's plan to process migrants outside the EU, highlighting conflicts between Italian and European immigration laws.
title: Italian judges deal new blow to Albania migrant scheme

description: Like in France, farmers' organizations in Belgium and Poland are denouncing the free trade agreement negotiated between the European Union and the MERCOSUR countries. Action is being planned.
title: Agricultural problems persist in Europe as farmers plan protests

description: Here's a photo review of the four typhoons that hit the Southeast Asian country, killing nearly 160 people and devastating the northern region of the archipelago.
title: Typhoon Toraji hit the Philippines on Monday, fourth storm in a month

description: Romain Weikmans, an international relations professor, explains the obstacles to financial transfers between global North and South countries to fund the green transition, a core issue of the Baku climate conference.
title: COP29: 'Supporting the fight against climate change in the global South is not one of the North's priorities'

description: For over a year, almost all the 25,000 inhabitants of the town on the border with Lebanon have fled the region. The families, scattered throughout Israeli territory, are housed in hotels, with no clear vision of their future.
title: In northern Israel, Kiryat Shmona's displaced lose hope of return

description: Seriously implicated in four separate criminal cases, Trump will now likely be able to avoid the trials that would have awaited him if he had lost the election.
title: What happens to Donald Trump's legal cases now?

description: Francis is expected on the French island around December 14-15. However, he has declined an invitation to Paris to attend the reopening of Notre-Dame a week before, which has irritated the French presidency.
title: Pope's planned visit to Corsica sparks tension

description: Following a The Washington Post report that claimed that President-elect Donald Trump had spoken about the war in Ukraine with Vladimir Putin, notably pushing against escalation and planning discussions on its 'resolution,' the Kremlin issued a denial.
title: Kremlin denies reported Trump-Putin call about Ukraine

description: Tom Homan, the former acting director of US Immigration and Customs Enforcement under Donald Trump's first presidency, will be tasked with overseeing the mass deportations that were a core campaign promise.
title: Trump says former ICE director Tom Homan will be appointed 'border czar'

description: In its provisional report on the state of the climate in 2024, published on Monday, November 11, the World Meteorological Organization said global average temperatures will be 1.54°C warmer than the preindustrial era. It issued 'the maximum alert in the face of the unbridled pace of climate change.'
title: 2024 will be hottest year on record and exceed 1.5°C warming for first time

description: The Commonwealth War Graves Commission honors the memory of fallen members of the former British Empire around the world. In France, 400 of the institution's employees watch over the resting places of the 575,000 people killed on French soil.
title: In France's military cemeteries, soldiers of the British Empire and the guardians of their memory

description: Under the US Constitution, the Senate must vote to approve nominations made by the president for senior executive positions, such as cabinet posts and judicial appointments. A constitutional clause, however, allows for presidents to bypass a Senate vote if the chamber is in an extended recess.
title: Trump demands Senate bypass votes to confirm appointees

description: Donald Trump's election comes as geopolitical tensions run high and the US faces a sluggish economy. The challenge at this year's COP will be to reach an agreement on financing to keep climate negotiations on track.
title: COP29 opens in a more perilous context than ever for the climate

description: The leaders of the first wave of Jewish immigration to Palestine at the end of the 19th century were already in no doubt about the inevitability of conflict with the land's Arab population.
title: Lessons from the first Jewish immigrants to Palestine

description: The EU is calling for an independent investigation into irregularities in the voting process  on October 26. However, it does not intend to take a position on the election's legitimacy, much to the disappointment of the opposition, which is pro-European. The pro-Russian ruling party has been in power since 2012.
title: EU ambivalence towards Georgia's disputed parliamentary elections

description: Nearly 30 dissidents, journalists and trade unionists have been arrested in recent months ahead of COP29, while the country sees the summit as an opportunity to improve its reputation on the international stage.
title: COP29: Azerbaijan wants to improve its image without giving up oil

description: On the eve of commemorating the Armistice of November 11, 1918, 'The Morning List' takes you on a journey to explore locations ideal for contemplation and reflection.
title: Five peace gardens in France at sites of the Great War

description: Sickened by Paris' diplomatic and military support for its Armenian rival, Baku retaliated by arresting three French nationals and launching an anti-French media campaign in its overseas territories.
title: COP29: An unprecedented crisis between France and Azerbaijan
